Athletes under scanner | Beijing 2008 | Sports | The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata)
                                                                                                                                                                                                             Athletes under scanner 
            BEIJING BYTES                
	The US will conduct a post-mortem into a disappointing Olympic athletics performance that has seen US sprinters eclipsed by their Jamaican rivals, the chief executive officer of USA Track amp; Field said. Once the Games are complete, we will be conducting a comprehensive review of all our programmes, Doug Logan said.         
	Fame game         
	A worldwide media survey on Friday showed that Michael Phelps, is the most famous figure at the Games. But Lin Miaoke, the little girl who lip-synched at the opening ceremony is catching up fast. A Texas-based Global Language Monitor, analysed the global media to see whose name gets mentioned most, and came up with the results.         
	Eye on Becks         
	England footballer David Beckham will take centre stage when the Olympic flag is handed to London at Sundays closing ceremony in Beijing. He will take part in London 2012s eight-minute slot in the Games finale designed to showcase the next host city.         
	Coe praise         
	London 2012 chief Sebastian Coe believes the Chinese didnt get much wrong in their organisation of the Beijing Games despite widespread criticism that these have been the no fun Olympics.         
	Suspended         
	Lyudmila Blonska was stripped of her Olympic heptathlon silver medal and suspended on Friday, the highest profile athlete kicked out of the Beijing Games so far for doping.                                                                                                                                              
